originalText.text: Truly disappointed in Cosmic Fisher Locks as a local business I want to see them and many others be successful. I received a quote and approved scope on October 18th for a project with a 50% deposit paid same day. 22 days later (today) they refused to carry out the work, told me they did not wish to do business with me, and said some unpleasant words in the process. They had to measure twice, never completed the project and left a bad taste in my mouth. They did return the deposit but I do not trust their word now or their quotes. A quote and contract is useless if not honored. Unprofessional, what a shame.

originalText.text:
I went here to get a brass key duplicated. The key cutter was not super friendly and sounded very condescending but did the job quickly and well.

I asked him why the key cost $7—he smirked and said he matched the original brass “real” key blank to make sure it works correctly.

He wouldn’t bother fixing my Home Depot keys that didn’t fit correctly.

I didn’t feel great when leaving the store because I thought I was overcharged and didn’t like the “old school” condescending tone—but went to another key duplication place and realized Cosmic Fischer was legit and price was right for midtown Manhattan.

I would recommend this store for the locksmithing and key duplication. Don’t go expecting a friendly chat.

I think the staff/owner could use some training on customer service and friendly communication. It would serve them well to survive as the mom and pop shop they ask us to protect.

originalText.text: I purchased a lock and installation from Cosmic. Fourteen months later the lock failed. I went to Cosmic and spoke with the owner. Although the lock was only warrantied for three months, Cosmic was willing to communicate with me and was sympathetic with my dissatisfaction. Ultimately they replaced and installed the lock cylinder free of charge. I greatly appreciate this company's willingness to respond to the individual situation so professionally and to sometimes compromise in the face of strict policy. Thank you Cosmic Fischer Locks for a job well done!

originalText.text: I was locked out of my apartment when I got back from work. I searched for a locksmith on google, and called Comic Fischer Locks.  They quickly replaced my lock and were professional and friendly. I’m a happy customer.
